  "body": "### Describe the feature\n\nIt would be useful if the network helpers would support running on anvil. \r\n\r\nThe `anvil_*` namespace is an alias for `hardhat_*` in the anvil node, so hardhat's custom methods should work. However the network helpers all check via `getHardhatProvider` that they are being ran on a hardhat network and error out if they are not (https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-network-helpers/src/utils.ts#L40).\r\n\r\nI understand if you don't want to support/test on anvil, in which case having a way of bypassing the `checkIfHardhatNetwork` should suffice for people interested in using the helpers on anvil while not adding too much burden on the hardhat team.\r\n\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
